Variables in java

[Variables in java](https://www.flowerbrackets.com/variables-in-java/)

Variable is a container which holds value in a java program. It is a name of memory location.

Syntax:

datatype variableName = value;

To declare a variable, first write data type; Data type can be integer, float, double, long etc. followed by variable name then its value. Like this,

int number = 7; // here number is variable

For more on variables in java click here - https://www.flowerbrackets.com/variables-in-java/
